<paragraph id="F9DF2AE22195D8DFBBDC197CDD38E4C5" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
99. 
<taxonomicName id="3D974E3C811B4D7957368D18B682EAB4" LSID="28950B14-5640-5D32-8240-9D1E3B41EC2B" authority="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke 1882: 520)." authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus subspathulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subspathulatus">Convolvulus subspathulatus Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke 1882: 520).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6BB5286BCB848580055EA5EB973AAC6" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="type">
<paragraph id="8AC0C39F68913D993E982EABCC665789" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F69EB6BCFEDEC3FAB265DC6E82F6BA5" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
SOMALIA, 
<emphasis id="C4694309CD385941D845C7E8076AD6F3" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Hildebrandt</emphasis>
1312 (holotype B†).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F2E11AC8B9B99F4B28CF521C0B5CC9F0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph id="22AE0A6219B831783D3A7D655049427E" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2DD9FCF42E1849CAA2F0D881C9583F17" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
Perennial herb with prostrate or twining stems to 50 cm long, vegetative parts densely sericeous becoming golden-brown when old. Leaves shortly petiolate, 0.6-2 
<normalizedToken id="5A72B83BDAA4808BE6E1222A2DDAA8CC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.6-2 cm, suborbicular, apex rounded or, rarely, emarginate or obtuse, base cordate, margin entire; petioles 1-6 mm long. Flowers 2-5 in shortly pedunculate, bracteate heads; peduncles 0.4-1.5 cm; bracteoles 7-10 
<normalizedToken id="05476642F26BE2047069D86B05EDC76F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm, oblong-elliptic to ovate; outer sepals 5-7 
<normalizedToken id="0852990E8503FF823101A63F53F4CCD9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, oblong to obovate, villous; corolla 9-11 mm long, blue, unlobed, midpetaline bands pilose; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided 3 mm above base; stigmas 1.75-2 mm, narrowly cylindrical and thicker than style. Capsule glabrous; seeds glabrous, tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation id="0CA0673318125DFA358C89721AD14295" author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 235]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70C3BDBC52276E8141DD572963EC201B" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AB0D706FDF82E4E2E29F7F0DAB86BBC5" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="824B8738B9447FAD3F67AD432D5D8A33" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
Endemic to Somalia (
<emphasis id="971C7BC0AF927BB44E2DA1DF17C51E0B" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Thulin &amp; Warfa</emphasis>
4533, 5907; 
<emphasis id="2C5612D42A4FC36378626861A3E00008" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Friis et al</emphasis>
. 5024; 
<emphasis id="AFEDC790F3D16E490C958A3DD4D06338" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Revoil</emphasis>
s.n. [6/1883], 
<emphasis id="2C8AD1907E164438B5FA50429475047B" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Tardelli &amp; Bavazzano</emphasis>
502). On coastal sand dunes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E04AEEBEE12B48844B6CFA1256AFA965" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9156E07227DE8B4C27BCCE1EE622400B" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD47FB0A5DE79FE0E55007BF800A967A" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<bibRefCitation id="AC813E2A3917209BC777F463EE96FDC1" author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin (2006</bibRefCitation>
: 235) suggests that this species is scarcely different from 
<taxonomicName id="0439F6F1F12A0EA79FCF2BDF712B0CC1" authorityName="Verdc., Kew Bull. 12: 344. 1957. (Verdcourt" authorityYear="1957" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus jefferyi" order="Solanales" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefferyi">
<emphasis id="26FD2B3A254B99D053FF03F3E3D3F1D4" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Convolvulus jefferyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and his description of 
<taxonomicName id="AC1F98B1356B01025C1D1EF00163A0CB" authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus subspathulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subspathulatus">
<emphasis id="F21E720EE95F53267AD615D6A778742B" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Convolvulus subspathulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<emphasis id="5760DFA482D4AA157EF5C2E447088452" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Flora of Somalia</emphasis>
seems to anticipate uniting the two species. However the suborbicular leaf shape and sericeous indumentum serve to distinguish the two species easily.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
